2 February 2021 Croydon Park Club 55 Seymour St , Croydon Park
Your health information session is an opportunity to discuss your diabetes
with Diabetes NSW & ACT health professionals in a relaxed and supportive
environment. You can ask questions, get advice and take home resources to help
During your 60-minute appointment, you will have a brief one-on-one
consultation with three health professionals from Diabetes NSW & ACT: a
diabetes educator, exercise physiologist, and dietitian. Each health
professional will spend 15 minutes with you to answer any questions or discuss
any concerns you may have. Please note the information and advice is general
in nature, and these sessions do not replace the education provided by your
You can also bring along your blood glucose meter to have it checked for
calibration and accuracy, and get practical tips on using your meter with our
 _For people living with all types of diabetes._
We’ve implemented new measures to protect the safety and wellbeing of all
attendees and staff at our diabetes education events. Read about our new
_The National Diabetes Services Scheme (NDSS) is an initiative of the
Australian Government and is administered by Diabetes Australia. The NDSS
agent in NSW & ACT is Diabetes NSW & ACT. Find out more about the NDSS at
ndss.com.au or call the NDSS Helpline on 1800 637 700._
